{"word":"ἐπάξιος","slug":"ἐπάξιος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>ἐπάξιος</b></el> <el>(ἐπ-άξιος, η, ον) </el><p/><div class='li500'><b>I. </b><i>worthy, deserving of</i>, <el>τινος</el> <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:—<a href='S:cum'>c.</a> <a href='S:infinitive'>inf.</a>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li500'><b>II. </b>of things, <i>deserved, meet</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b>, <a href='S:et cetera'>etc.</a>; <el>κυρεῖν τῶν ἐπαξίων</el> to meet <i>with one's deserts</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>:—so, <a href='S:Adverb'>adv.</a> <el>-ίως</el>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b><i>worth mentioning</i>, <b><a href='S:Herodotus'>Hdt.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}